#architecture_hunter 
Accordingly to @omniviewdesign, “the main ambition behind the design of the Villa, was to create a home that combines a strong sense of centricity with flowing connections to its natural environment.

To achieve this, the model of the ancient Greek home was studied carefully as a departure point. In fact, the massing and master planning of spiral Villa Is very close to the ancient Greek home.

The ancient Greek geometry of the spiral has been used to organize and Reinvent this master plan as a sequence of activities. The flow of the spiral represents a spectrum from private to public and ends in the Centrepoint.

There, The Villa features an abstraction or the ancient Greek "Hestia", which in this case is materialized as a central exterior sitting under the shade of an olive tree.

This way the goal of the ancient Greek house to offer privatized exterior space is realized, but at the same time strong relationships to the peripheral functions are created •
.
.
.
.
.
.

This year, due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Casacor, an exhibition of architecture, design and decoration that takes place annually in several cities in Brazil and the world, had to be different.

#CasacorJanelas invited several architects and designers to design spaces inside containers, placed in different spots of the city.

In this edition, LG @lgdobrasil proposed Suite Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos to design the “Connected House”, the container located in Praça Cidade de Milão, with landscape designing by Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

In the kitchen, the architects specified the LG Studio Line appliances, in addition to the Smart LG Side by Side Inverter refrigerator. In the living room, they artistically composed the wall with frames and also with: the LG 65 ”4K OLED HDR Smart TV, awarded as the best TV on the market, the mirrored Artcool air conditioning and the Multi Artcool Gallery.

“LG Connected House” also has other sophisticated products of the brand. Check everything else here: lg.com/br/casa-cor

————

Neste ano, por conta da Pandemia do COVID-19, a Casacor, uma mostra de arquitetura, design e decoração que acontece anualmente em várias cidades do Brasil e do mundo, teve que ser diferente. 

A Casacor Janelas propôs convidar diversos arquitetos e designers para projetarem espaços dentro de containers, espalhados em toda a cidade. 

Nesta edição a LG @lgdobrasil chamou a Suíte Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos para desenhar a “Casa Conectada LG”, cujo container fica na Praça Cidade de Milão, com projeto paisagístico de Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

Na cozinha, os arquitetos especificaram os eletrodomésticos da Linha Studio LG, além da geladeira Smart LG Side by Side Inverter. 
Já na sala de estar, artisticamente entre os quadros compuseram a parede com: a Smart TV LG 65” 4K OLED HDR, eleita a melhor TV do mercado, o ar condicionado Artcool espelhado e o Multi Artcool Gallery. 

A “Casa Conectada LG” ainda conta com demais sofisticados produtos da marca. Confira tudo aqui: lg.com/br/casa-cor

_project: Bridge House 
_architecture: @nomostudio.eu 
_photographer: @adriagoulaphoto 
_location: Es Mercadal, Menorca, #Spain 

“Its generous plot of 2400sqm allows the dwelling to stretch horizontally to capture the surrounding’s best landscape views. At the same time, its rotating volumes create surprising interior spaces and never repeating outlooks. Based on the assembly of squared and pentagonal plans, these small polyhydric volumes stack and hover over the existing landscape with playful lightness. Their bridge-like composition gives the house its name. Breaking down the program into smaller units seemed a more respectful way to place a large program onto the site. The outer terraces and pool are designed as a direct extension of the indoor plan, following its same geometries and keeping the vast majority of the plot untouched” say the architects.

“In a contrast to the transparent steel and glass façade of the structure, the interior is completely clad in oak like a wooden box. Despite the all-around glazing, this creates a warm atmosphere and a feeling of security without disturbing the direct connection to the surrounding nature. The result is a modern, cubic building with high architectural standards that takes advantage of the difficult slope. Self-confident, with clear, almost strict lines, the house stages itself and the surrounding landscape” say the architects.
